2500|$|In {{the sixth}} reading ( [...] , aliyah), Lamech <b>told</b> <b>his</b> <b>wives</b> {{that he had}} slain a lad for {{bruising}} him, and that if Cain was avenged sevenfold, then Lamech should be avenged seventy-sevenfold. Adam and Eve had a third son and named him Seth, meaning [...] "God has provided me with another offspring in place of Abel." [...] Seth had a son named Enosh, and then men began to invoke the Lord by name. A closed portion ( [...] , setumah) ends here {{with the end of}} chapter ...|$|R
